events.name: Intro to Kotlin: Kotlin Koans Workshop
events.description:
Please bring your laptop to this meetup! (Snacks provided)

Agenda:
5:00-6:00 Announcements/ Intro to Kotlin: Kotlin Koans Workshop - Led by: Sarah Pham, Jay Patel, and Nick Sargsyan
6:00-7:00 Mini hackathon for Google Home Mini using Kotlin and lessons learned

About the Workshop:
This tutorial walks you through a series of exercises to get familiar with Kotlin.

Kotlin Koans are a series of exercises to get you familiar with the Kotlin Syntax. Each exercise is created as a failing unit test and your job is to make it pass. You can work with Kotlin Koans in one of three ways.

You can play with Koans online (https://play.kotlinlang.org/koans).
You can solve the tasks right inside IntelliJ IDEA or Android Studio by installing the EduTools plugin (https://www.jetbrains.com/help/education/install-edutools-plugin.html) and choosing Kotlin Koans course (https://www.jetbrains.com/help/education/learner-start-guide.html?section=Kotlin%20Koans).
You can clone the project on GitHub (https://github.com/Kotlin/kotlin-koans). You can open this project in IntelliJ IDEA, or work with it from the command line using your favourite editor. Note that to work with Koans from Android Studio, use the EduTools plugin.

Whatever way you choose to solve koans, you can see the solution for each task. In the online version and inside EduTools plugin you'll find the button "Show answer". The GitHub repository has two branches, master which contains the exercises for you to do and resolutions which contains the resolved exercises. We recommend checking the solution after you implement the task to compare your solution with the proposed one.

events.name: Firebase Study Jam
events.description:
We are hosting our first online meetup, it will be hosted via Zoom meeting. All the instruction to join Zoom meeting is written in the description section at last.

Join a community of like-minded developers and explore the latest Firebase for Web technologies as a team. Want to get started building web apps? Learn how to do that with Firebase!

Join us for our Firebase Study Jam! Together we'll work through Firebase for web codelabs prepared by Google instructors. You will be able to get hands-on experience with Firebase. Also, Learn How to use Cloud Firestore for your web projects?

Attend Zoom meeting with a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of popular browsers.

For the best experience check out Get Started with Firebase for Web - https://firebase.google.com/docs/web/setup

Agenda:

05:00 to 05:15 - Join the Zoom meeting & Networking
05:15 to 06:15 - Codelab: Get to know Firebase for web (From, Nikolay S)
06:15 to 06:30 - Break
06:30 to 07:00 - Everything you need to know about Firebase
07:00 to 08:00 - Hands-on & Codelab: Cloud Firestore (From, Jay P)

Join from PC, Mac, Linux, iOS or Android: https://auburn.zoom.us/j/8615604503
Connect using Computer/Device audio if possible.

upcoming.name: IWD 2020 | International Women's Day [ONLINE]
upcoming.description:
Our April meetup celebrates International Women's Day. This is especially for women in tech, and male allies! Come enjoy an evening of getting to know your community and yourself!

International Women's Day (IWD) is on annually on March 8th, all over the world the celebration focuses on different aspects of appreciation towards strong women and their achievements. On April 14th we invite you to share your superpowers - those qualities that make you shine! Together let us celebrate the super-women in our lives and create a new narrative for women in our industry.

- Women Speaker
- Icebreakers
- Define your goals for 2020
- Socialize!
